@Orichalkos:  
Allies' abilities are triggered abilities because they trigger when an event happens (an ally hits the battlefield). The allies that require you to tap to activate the ability, such as [Harabaz Druid](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Harabaz Druid) and [Sea Gate Loremaster](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sea Gate Loremaster).  

Great card, though undercosted. 5 mana would be more appropriate I'd think. Run with [Tajuru Preserver](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tajuru Preserver) in standard if you want a good way of shutting down most of your opponents.
